The Gombe State Governor-elect, Alhaji Muhammad Inuwa Yahaya, has inaugurated a 30-member swearing-in and inauguration committee to be chaired by Sen. Joshua Lidani. The committee has Alhaji Abubakar Mu’azu Hassan as deputy chairman, while Alhaji Ibrahim Dasuki Jalo Waziri will serve as secretary. Inaugurating the committee at the weekend, the governor-elect said its term of reference was to ensure smooth conduct of the swearing in ceremony on May 29. He called on the members of the committee to liaise with a committee to be constituted by the outgoing Ibrahim Hassan Dankwambo administration for a successful handing over. PDP governors, Mu’azu absent at inauguration of post election review c’ttee PDP governors, Mu'azu boycott inauguration of post-election review c'ttee Yobe inaugurates transition committee Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin